# A [[sentry]] or [[guard]].
# (computer science) a phrase of unique characters (a [[string]]), used to mark a document for processing by a computer program. For example, an [[HTML]] tag such as '&lt;table&gt;' is a form of sentinel as its a unique phrase that is non-reaccuring in the english language. However the use of '&lt;' and 'table' do occur in english but not in this form, so '&lt;table&gt;' is a relatively good sentinel phrase.

